      /* Energy Platform Launch */
      'news.epl.meta': 'March 2026',
      'news.epl.h1': 'SimDyns Launches Updated Energy Management Platform with Enhanced Monitoring and Analytics',
      'news.epl.h4a': 'Energy Management · Digital Platform · ISO 50001',
      'news.epl.p1': '<strong>SimDyns Technology Solutions</strong> is pleased to announce the launch of its significantly updated <strong>Energy Management Platform</strong> — a web-based solution purpose-built for industrial organisations seeking to monitor, analyse, and optimise their energy consumption in real time.',
      'news.epl.p2': 'The updated platform brings a range of new and enhanced capabilities, building on the foundation developed under the EU SeeBridge grant programme. It is designed to support full <strong>ISO 50001 compliance</strong> and provides operational teams with the tools they need to drive continuous energy performance improvement.',
      'news.epl.h4b': "What's New in the Updated Platform",
      'news.epl.list': '<li><strong>Enhanced Real-Time Monitoring:</strong> Improved dashboards delivering live visibility into energy consumption across multiple sites, systems, and equipment categories.</li><li><strong>Advanced Energy Performance Indicators (EnPIs):</strong> Configurable KPIs aligned with ISO 50001, enabling teams to track efficiency trends and benchmark performance over time.</li><li><strong>Significant Energy Use (SEU) Management:</strong> Dedicated modules to identify, monitor, and manage the systems and processes with the highest energy impact.</li><li><strong>Forecasting and Anomaly Detection:</strong> Data-driven forecasting tools that flag abnormal consumption patterns and support proactive intervention before costs escalate.</li><li><strong>Improved Reporting Suite:</strong> Automated report generation for management reviews, regulatory submissions, and sustainability disclosures.</li><li><strong>Multi-User Access and Role Management:</strong> Granular access controls allowing energy managers, engineers, and executives to work within a shared platform at appropriate permission levels.</li>',
      'news.epl.p3': 'The platform is accessible via any modern web browser with no installation required, making it straightforward to deploy across facilities of any scale.',
      'news.epl.btn': 'Explore the Live Platform →',
      'news.epl.p4': 'Organisations interested in deploying the SimDyns Energy Management Platform for their operations — or in a tailored demonstration — are encouraged to <a href="../../contact/index.html" style="color:var(--teal); font-weight:600;">contact our team</a>.',

      /* Horizon Europe */
      'news.hor.meta': 'January 2026',
      'news.hor.h1': 'SimDyns Joins Horizon Europe 2026 Consortium to Expand Cross-Border Investment Ecosystems',
      'news.hor.h4a': 'Horizon Europe · Innovation Ecosystems · Deep Tech',
      'news.hor.p1': '<strong>SimDyns Technology Solutions</strong> has joined an international consortium applying under the <strong>Horizon Europe call HORIZON-EIE-2026-01-CONNECT-02</strong> — Expanding Investment Ecosystems — coordinated by <strong>Octa Insight AS (Norway)</strong>. The proposed project, titled <em>"Investment Bridge: Expanding Venture Connectivity for Digital, Health and Circular Innovation"</em>, is submitted under the EU\'s Interconnected Innovation Ecosystems programme (2026.1) as a 24-month Coordination and Support Action.',
      'news.hor.p2': 'The project brings together partners from Norway, Türkiye, Bulgaria, Portugal, and the UK to build a cross-border investment-driven ecosystem linking strong EU innovation regions with emerging innovator ecosystems. The consortium includes <strong>OSTIM</strong> and <strong>Gazi University</strong> (Türkiye), <strong>TU Varna</strong> and <strong>Bulgaria Business Forums</strong> (Bulgaria), <strong>Ankara Medipol University</strong>, and <strong>FastTrack</strong> (Portugal/UK).',
      'news.hor.h4b': 'Project Objectives',
      'news.hor.p3': 'The core ambition of the Investment Bridge project is to unlock venture capital flows between strong EU regions and emerging ecosystems, with a focus on three strategic sectors:',
      'news.hor.list': '<li><strong>Digital Transformation</strong> — connecting start-ups and scale-ups to strong-region investors and accelerators</li><li><strong>Health Systems Innovation</strong> — MedTech, digital health, and hospital-linked buyer engagement</li><li><strong>Circular Economy</strong> — sustainability-driven manufacturing, waste management, and municipal partnerships</li>',
      'news.hor.p4': 'A central deliverable is the <strong>Dual Investment Gateway</strong> — an interactive platform providing regulatory, fiscal, and market intelligence to help investors enter emerging ecosystems and to guide start-ups on EU market access requirements.',
      'news.hor.h4c': "SimDyns' Role in the Consortium",
      'news.hor.p5': 'SimDyns contributes its expertise in <strong>deep tech training, engineering simulation, and energy management</strong> to the consortium\'s innovation acceleration workstream. Our experience in delivering EQF-aligned training programmes — including AI-powered cybersecurity and CubeSat courses in partnership with EIT Deep Tech — positions SimDyns to support investment-readiness bootcamps, technical mentoring, and the development of EU-ready start-up pipelines across the consortium\'s target regions.',
      'news.hor.p6': 'The project submission deadline was <strong>20 January 2026</strong>. SimDyns looks forward to contributing to this pan-European collaboration and to strengthening the link between deep tech capability and cross-border investment opportunity.',

